From: "Eric W. Biederman" <ebiederm@xmission.com>
Date: Fri, 14 Mar 2014 18:11:22 -0700
Subject: [PATCH v2 229/244] sfc: Don't receive packets when the napi budget ==
 0
Patch-mainline: v3.15-rc1
Git-commit: 75363a4676cdb046242d06dca6e8a9c0a20d6c4a
References: bsc#909618 FATE#317521

Processing any incoming packets with a with a napi budget of 0
is incorrect driver behavior.

This matters as netpoll will shortly call drivers with a budget of 0
to avoid receive packet processing happening in hard irq context.

Signed-off-by: "Eric W. Biederman" <ebiederm@xmission.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/ef10.c  |    3 +++
 drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/farch.c |    3 +++
 2 files changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/ef10.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/ef10.c
@@ -1955,6 +1955,9 @@ static int efx_ef10_ev_process(struct ef
 	int tx_descs = 0;
 	int spent = 0;
 
+	if (quota <= 0)
+		return spent;
+
 	read_ptr = channel->eventq_read_ptr;
 
 	for (;;) {
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/farch.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/sfc/farch.c
@@ -1257,6 +1257,9 @@ int efx_farch_ev_process(struct efx_chan
 	int tx_packets = 0;
 	int spent = 0;
 
+	if (budget <= 0)
+		return spent;
+
 	read_ptr = channel->eventq_read_ptr;
 
 	for (;;) {
